  <scenario>
    <description>This scenario puts a formation of M1 Abrams tanks headed due south.
       
The M1 Abrams are air-to-ground targets, you can damage them with bombs or heavy guns.  Can you stop them before they reach downtown Kansas City?
			
Start at the Charles B Wheeler Downtown Airport in Kansas City and go due east from the airport a couple of miles, looking along the south bank of the river in the East Bottoms. The formation of 11 tanks starts there and moves about about 6PM directly towards downtown.

When you bomb and shoot the tanks they will slow down, finally catch fire, and then stop completely (to see the smoke and fire you must have Particles enabled in View/Rendering Options).

To damage the tanks takes a direct hit from a machine gun or heavy gun, or a close strike by a heavy bomb.
			
Approximate lat and long of starting point of the tank formation: 39.145,-94.518
			
Install this scenario in the FlightGear/data/AI directory.  The scenario requires the improved M-1 Abrams Tank AI model to be installed in FG/Aircraft.		

Any aircraft that shoots guns or drops bombs can damage the tanks.  The Fairchild A-10 Thunderbolt is a great choice - http://wiki.flightgear.org/index.php/Fairchild_A-10 </description>
